column3: REVISED ESTIMATED RESIDENT POPULATION MID-1974 ON 1981 BOUNDARIES
NO WARRANTY IS GIVEN BY ONS AS TO THE ACCURACY OR COMPREHENSIVENESS OF THE DATA
It is ONS policy to publish population estimates rounded to at least the nearest hundred persons. Estimates are
sometimes provided in units to facilitate further calculations (eg to DOE/WO for calculation of Standard Spending
Assessments used in the distribution of Revenue Support Grant, or as denominator for mortality rates). Unit estimates
cannot be accurate to that level of detail.
